title: Heuristics - Intelligent Search Strategies for Computer Problem
description:
Content:

- Problem-solving strategies and the nature of Heuristic information.
- Heuristics and problem representations. Basic Heuristic-Search procedures.
- Formal properties of Heuristic methods. Heuristics viewed as information provided - by simplified models.
- Performance analysis of Heuristic methods.
- Abstract models for quantitative performance analysis.
- Complexity versus precision of admissible Heuristics.
- Searching with non admissible Heuristics.
- Game-playing programs.
- Strategies and models for game-playing programs.
- Performance analysis for game-searching strategies.
- Decision quality in game searching.
